HEADWORD: Gammer
<hw>Gam"mer</hw> <pr>(g⟦acr⟧m"m⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Possibly contr. fr. <ets>godmother</ets>; but prob. fr.
<ets>grammer</ets> for <ets>grandmother</ets>. Cf.
<er>Gaffer</er>.]</ety> <def>An old wife; an old woman; -- correlative
of <contr>gaffer</contr>, an old man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

